The paper deals with stochastic approximation schemes, which are commonly studied in the control theory and optimization literature, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also deals with the presence of non-additive iterate-dependent Markov noise, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of the asymptotic behavior of the recursion, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of differential inclusions, which is a topic of interest in numerical analysis and scientific computing (cs.NA). Finally, the paper involves the study of set-valued functions, which is a topic of interest in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
